<h2 id="business-question">Business Question</h2>
<p>Before we start loading our data on Pandas and analytizing it, letâ€™s first understand our business question and our data. The dataset was originally used by <a href="https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s00521-018-3523-0">Sakar et al</a> to propose a real-time online shopper behavior analysis system. The goal of the paper was the predict the purchasing intention of the customer and Web site abandonment likelihood. In this series, weâ€™ll stick to the former and analyze and predict which behaviors of a customer will result to a higher likelihood of making a purchase.</p>

<h2 id="dataloading-and-understanding-the-data">Dataloading and Understanding the Data</h2>
<p>Letâ€™s load our data and understand it. There are 10 numerical and 8 categorical attributes, where the â€œRevenueâ€ column is indicates a purchase. This will be our indepednent variable.</p>

<p>Iâ€™ll be lazy here and quote the UCI Machine Learning Repository Description.</p>

